Done: `coworker-scheduler.ps1` now supports per-task `PendingPaths`, so the scheduler skips launching child PowerShell processes when the coworker or draft-refinement queues are empty; I also documented the new config behavior in `coworker/README*.md`.
Validated with a targeted temporary-config harness (`coworker-scheduler.ps1 -Once`) that confirmed empty queues stay in `WaitingForWork` without launching a worker, while queued files still trigger a successful run; `coworker-scheduler.config.psd1` also imports cleanly.
